Sniffing

binomial.sniff <- rep(0, nrow(xdata))
binomial.sniff[xdata$ProportionSniffed > 0] <- 1

GLMM

glmm.all <- glmer(binomial.sniff ~ xdata$ColorVisionType + log.scent.increase + xdata$chem.dist.RF.URF + log.RG + log.BY + log.LUM +  (1|xdata$Animal) + (1|xdata$ScientificName), family = "binomial")

Calculating variance exaplained

var.fixed <- var(as.vector(fixef(glmm.all)%*%t(glmm.all@pp$X))) #variance fixed effects

var.random <- sum(unlist(VarCorr(glmm.all))) #variance random effects

var.residual <- attr(VarCorr(glmm.all), "sc")^2 #Residual variance

Fixed effects:

var.fixed/(var.fixed + var.random + var.residual)
## [1] 0.4491705

Total model (fixed and random effects)

(var.fixed + var.random) / (var.fixed + var.random + var.residual)
## [1] 0.9072974

Model Diagnostics

Comparison to null model

glmm.null <- glmer(binomial.sniff ~  (1|xdata$Animal) + (1|xdata$ScientificName), family = "binomial")

anova(glmm.null, glmm.all, test="Chisq")

colfunc <- colorRampPalette(c("lightpink", "darkred"))
color.palette <- colfunc(101)
cols <- rep("a", length(binomial.sniff))


for (i in 1:nrow(xdata)) {
  
  cur.perc <- 1+round(100*(log.RG[i]-min(log.RG))/(max(log.RG)-min(log.RG)))
  cols[i] <- color.palette[cur.perc]
  
}



par( lwd = 4)
plot(jitter.numeric.col.vision, jitter.binomial.sniff, pch = 19, xaxt = "n", yaxt = "n", ylab = "", xlab = "", cex = 0.4, lwd = 1, col = adjustcolor(cols, alpha.f = 0.6))
